tickets.description:
As discussed on TEI-L on 2008-10-30 \(subject: "markup inside &lt;am&gt;?"\).

It seems that at least transcription-type elements \(add, corr, del, hi, sic, subst, supplied, unclear\) ought to be available within &lt;am&gt;. Some examples of usage \(taken from real texts, not just made up exempli gratia\):

&lt;abbr&gt;Aug&lt;am&gt;g&lt;unclear&gt;g&lt;/unclear&gt;&lt;/am&gt;&lt;/abbr&gt;
&lt;expan&gt;Augusti tres&lt;/expan&gt;

&lt;abbr&gt;Imp&lt;am&gt;pp&lt;supplied&gt;pp&lt;/supplied&gt;&lt;/am&gt;&lt;/abbr&gt;
&lt;expan&gt;Imperatores quinque&lt;/expan&gt;

&lt;abbr&gt;Imp&lt;am&gt;p&lt;sic&gt;p&lt;/sic&gt;&lt;/am&gt;&lt;/abbr&gt;
&lt;expan&gt;Imperatores duo&lt;/expan&gt;

&lt;abbr&gt;lampr&lt;am&gt;&lt;unclear&gt;&lt;g ref="\#leaf"/&gt;&lt;/unclear&gt;&lt;/am&gt;&lt;/abbr&gt;
&lt;expan&gt;lamprotates&lt;/expan&gt;

Do we need some discussion to decide which elements or element classes need to be included, perhaps? Or is all phrase-level potentially useful?

